            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PIZZAZZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">45</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">25</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Both</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUIZZIFY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">42</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">32</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">SOWPODS</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">QUIZZICAL</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">40</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400">30</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Both</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-2">* Realistic score accounts for blanks (0 pts) substituting extra Z tiles</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Blank Reality Check</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">⚠️ Important</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The "theoretical" scores assume all Z tiles are real Z's (10 pts each). In practice, there's <span class="text-white font-medium">only one Z tile</span> in the bag. Words with 2+ Z's need blanks (worth 0 points). PIZZAZZ theoretically scores 45, but realistically <span class="text-white font-medium">scores 25</span> with two blanks as Z. Still excellent for a 7-letter word!</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Realistic 40+ Plays</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">A 20-point word on DWS = 40 points. A 14-point word on TWS = 42 points. Premium squares are the realistic path to 40+ in most games.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ The Trap</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Don't hold tiles hoping for PIZZAZZ. The chance of drawing Z + both blanks + P, I, A is astronomically low. Play high-value words as they appear.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Focus on premium squares instead:</span> In practice, 40+ point turns come from 15-20 point words landing on DWS or TWS — not from 40+ base-value words. Master premium square positioning for consistent high scores.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">QUIZZICAL is the most achievable:</span> With Q + Z + blank (as second Z) + common tiles U, I, I, C, A, L — this 9-letter word scoring 30 realistic points is the most playable entry in the 40+ club.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Bingo bonus transforms everything:</span> QUIZZICAL as a bingo = 30 pts + 50 bonus = 80 points. That's a game-winning play from a single turn — achievable maybe once in 100 games, but devastating when it hits.</p>
        </div>
